/**
 * \page exchanger_config Configuration of yaxt exchanger method
   \tableofcontents

\section exchanger_config_intro Introduction

All data exchanges between processes during the interpolation are done using
<a href="https://dkrz-sw.gitlab-pages.dkrz.de/yaxt/">yaxt</a>. It supports
multiple methods to execute these exchanges. Depending on the system
configuration different methods may have varying performance characteristics.

Available exchanger names and their specifics can be found in the
<a href="https://dkrz-sw.gitlab-pages.dkrz.de/yaxt/da/dec/defaults.html">yaxt documentation</a>.

\section exchanger_config_how How to configure yaxt exchanger method?

The yaxt exchanger method can be configured by an environment variable, which
can be set before the start of the program or during runtime (but before
\ref phase_enddef) by using, for example, the Standard C library routine
\c setenv. This sets the default method for all interpolations.

<b>YAC_YAXT_EXCHANGER</b>=\<exchanger_name\>

Alternatively, the exchanger method can be set explicitly for each
individual coupling, either via the
\ref yaml_yaxt_exchanger_name "configuration file" or the
\ref phase_def_couple "user interface" depending on the definition method of
the couple.

*/

